P.L. Sperr.

Riverside Park, north from a point near West 103rd Street, showing paths and embankments in this narrow garden spot that parallels the North (Hudson) River. The New York Central Railroad tracks seen, will in 1938 be moved slightly eastward and covered over; their former site and marginal land being landscaped in the West Side Improvement Project. This set consists of 3 views from different angles; No. 3 of which is several years later.

Views 1 & 2:-April 3, 1932.
View 3:-June 17, 1934.
